<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900920-0129</DOCNO><DOCID>900920-0129.</DOCID><HL>   Arkla to Boost Spending</HL><DATE>09/20/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9</SO><CO>   ARK</CO><IN>OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><LP>   HOUSTON -- Arkla Exploration Co. said it would increaseits 1990 exploration and production capital spending budgetby 27%, to $70 million, from $55 million.   The company said it drilled 73 new natural gas and oilwells during the first half of 1990, and that it expects&quot;activity in the second half of the year to somewhat exceedthe number of new wells drilled in the first half.&quot;</LP><TEXT/></DOC>